Base semiring class {cite}`goodman-1999-semiring`.

A semiring is defined by a tuple $<K, \oplus, \otimes, \mathbf{0}, \mathbf{1}>$.
$K$ is a set of values;
$\oplus$ is commutative, associative and has an identity element `0`;
$\otimes$ is associative, has an identity element `1` and distributes over `+`.
